title: -The Reaction Ni-58(N,P)Co-58 At Different Neutron Energies-

x4freetext: -THE REACTION NI-58(N,P)CO-58 AT DIFFERENT NEUTRON
ENERGIES-
6 MEV VAN DE GRAAFF, AND-
1.3 MEV COCKROFT-WALTON.
DEUTERIUM GAS TARGET, OR-
ZIRCONIUM-TRITIDE TARGET.
.FLUXES AND ENERGY SPREADS WERE AS FOLLOWS-
AT 8.4 MEV, FLUX 1.5E+08 N/SR.SEC IN THE FORWARD
DIRECTION, ENERGY SPREAD 200 KEV.
AT 14.1 MEV, FLUX 1.0E+08 N/SR.SEC AT 90 DEGREES
ENERGY SPREAD 200 KEV.
AT 22 MEV, FLUX 0.20E+08 N/SR.SEC IN THE FORWARD
DIRECTION, ENERGY SPREAD 300 KEV.
.NI-58 ENRICHED TO 99 PERCENT, THICKNESS 9.6 MG/CM-SQ
AT 8.4 MEV, 30 MG/CM-SQ AT THE OTHER ENERGIES.
.DIRECT DETECTION OF EMITTED PARTICLES.
COUNTER TELESCOPE CONSISTING OF TWO GAS
SCINTILLATORS AS DELTA-E COUNTERS, AND A
CSI(TL) CRYSTAL AS TOTAL ENERGY DETECTOR.
PROTON TELESCOPE CONSISTING OF POLYTHENE
RADIATOR AND CSI(TL) CRYSTAL TO MONITOR
THE FLUX.
LI6-I(EU) SCINTILLATOR ALSO USED TO MEASURE
THE NEUTRON FLUX.
MEASURED BY REPLACING NICKEL
TARGET BY POLYTHENE, NORMALIZATION VALUE NOT
GIVEN.
.MOST DATA FROM NEUDADA, SOME TAKEN DIRECTLY FROM
THE PUBLICATION.
DATA-ERR HEADING IN SUBWORK 007 CORRECTED.
.LABORATORY ENERGY SCALE CORRECTED FOR ENERGY LOSSES
IN THE DELTA-E DETECTORS AND TARGET AND TRANSFORMED
TO CENTRE OF MASS. COUNTS IN EACH CHANNEL ADJUSTED
TO GIVE SPECTRUM FOR EQUAL INTERVALS OF THE CENTRE
OF MASS SCALE.
GRAPHICAL DATA GIVEN IN PUBLICATION.
